briefdescription.para: Instantiate TrajectoryReader using a default configuration.

detaileddescription.para: Default reader configuration.
If you are reading BasePoints, this sets coordinates 0 to d-1 (D is the point's dimension) using columns 0 to d-1.
If you are reading TrajectoryPoints, column 0 is the object ID, column 1 is the timestamp, and columns 2 through D+1 (inclusive) are the coordinates.
These are the default settings. You can override any or all of them after you instantiate the reader.

briefdescription.para: Specify comment character for skipping lines.

detaileddescription.para: A line is a comment if and only if its first non-whitespace character is the comment character ('#' by default). We will skip such lines entirely. We do not handle inline or trailing comments: a line will either be included in its entirety or skipped completely.

briefdescription.para: Read trajectories from files.

detaileddescription.para: This reader wraps the following pipeline:

listitem.para: Read lines from a text file
Skip any lines that begin with a designated comment character ('#' by default)
Tokenize each line using specified delimiters (whitespace by default)
Create a trajectory (user-specified type) from each tokenized line
Return the resulting points via a C++ iterator

detaileddescription.para: You will use set_input() to supply an input stream, set_comment_character() to configure which lines to skip, set_field_delimiter() to specify how to turn lines into fields.
